    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fæjnæg" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>fæjnæg</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>доска</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>plank</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>fæjnægfars</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>крепкобокий</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>with sturdy sides</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>donyl ma fæjnæg rawaʒūt, kæd yl cæwag racæwid</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>перекиньте через реку доску, чтобы по ней мог перейти пешеход</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>throw a board over the river so that a pedestrian can cross it</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."
                            /><biblScope>194</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>agæ fæjnægæj æmbærzuni ǧud kæntæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>позаботьтесь о том, чтобы покрыть котел доской</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>take care to cover the cauldron with a board</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."
                                /><biblScope>33%l12–13%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Narti fæjnægfars xwarz Sozuruqo</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Нартовский крепкобокии славный Созуруко</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>glorious Sozuruko the Nart with sturdy sides</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."
                            /><biblScope>58%l159%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>rewi fæjnæg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>грудная клетка</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>thorax</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes."/><biblScope>99</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pānaka</w></mentioned>, от корня <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/>
                        <w>рā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>охранять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ограждать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/>
                        <gloss><q>служить оградой, щитом</q></gloss></mentioned>: ‘доска’ получила
                    название по своему использованию в качестве материала для ограждений и для
                    щитов. Для семантики ‘доска’ — ‘щит’ ср. <mentioned xml:lang="gmh"><lang/>
                        <w>bret</w></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>hord</w></mentioned>, совмещавшие значения ‘доска’ и ‘щит’, а также
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w>щитъ</w></mentioned>, исходное значение которого ‘дерево’, ‘доска’
                    выступает в <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>scît</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Scheit</w>
                        <gloss><q>дощечка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>обломок дерева</q></gloss></mentioned>. У скифо-меотских племен
                    „щиты делались из дерева“ (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н. Анфимов. Древние
                            поселения Прикубанья. 1953</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">N.
                            Anfimov. Ancient settlements of the Kuban region.
                        1953</biblScope></bibl>). %sТацит%s (<bibl><biblScope>Анн. II
                        14</biblScope></bibl>) пишет о древних германцах, что они в качестве щитов
                    пользовались „тонкими раскрашенными досками“ („%itenues et fucatas colore
                    tabulas%i“). Слово засвидетельствовано в %bскифском%b; ос. %ifæjnægfars%i
                    ‘крепкобокий’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЭп."
                            /><biblScope>58%l159%l</biblScope></bibl>) должно было звучать в
                    скифском %i*panak-pars%i; с обычной для скифского инверсией в сложных словах
                    имеем %ipars-panak%i в скифском собственном имени <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Παρσπάνακος</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>175,
                                235</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>175,
                                    235</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>. За пределами
                    скифо-осетинского ср. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>pānak</w>
                        <gloss><q>то, что ограждает, охраняет</q></gloss></mentioned> (в сложных
                    словах), отсюда <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>p'anak'</w>
                        <gloss><q>покров</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>защита</q></gloss></mentioned> (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>šāb-panah</w>
                        <gloss><q>ночной кров</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>приют</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pānah</w>
                        <gloss><q>деревянный дверной засов</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>клин</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>охрана</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>защита</q></gloss></mentioned> (в сложных словах), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāna-</w></mentioned> id. Может быть, сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>pon</w>
                        <gloss><q>крыша</q></gloss></mentioned>. %bРусск.%b (диал.) <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>пано́к</w>
                        <gloss><q>доска для лубочной картины</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">также</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">also</note>
                        <gloss><q>корытце для рубки мяса</q></gloss></mentioned> является, возможно,
                    скифским наследием.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>175,
                            176, 199, 212, 236</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pānaka</w></mentioned>, from the root <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/>
                        <w>рā-</w>
                        <gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/>
                        <gloss><q>enclose</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/>
                        <gloss><q>serve as a fence, as a shield</q></gloss></mentioned>: ‘plank’
                    received its name due to its use as a material for fences and shields. For the
                    semantics ‘plank’ — ‘shield’ cf. <mentioned xml:lang="gmh"><lang/>
                        <w>bret</w></mentioned> and <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>hord</w></mentioned>, which combined both meanings: ‘plank’ and ‘shield’,
                    and also <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w>щитъ</w></mentioned>, the initial meaning of which is ‘wood’, ‘plank’ is
                    in <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>scît</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Scheit</w>
                        <gloss><q>small plank</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>piece of wood</q></gloss></mentioned>. The shields of
                    Scythian-Maeotian tribes ‘were made of wood’ (<bibl><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Н.
                            Анфимов. Древние поселения Прикубанья. 1953</biblScope><biblScope
                            xml:lang="en">N. Anfimov. Ancient settlements of the Kuban region.
                            1953</biblScope></bibl>). %sTacit%s (<bibl><biblScope>Анн. II
                            14</biblScope></bibl>) wrote about ancient Germans that they used ‘thin
                    coloured planks’ („%itenues et fucatas colore tabulas%i“) as shields. The word
                    is attested in %bScythian%b; Ossetic %ifæjnægfars%i ‘with sturdy sides’
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЭп."
                            /><biblScope>58%l159%l</biblScope></bibl>) should have sounded in
                    Scythian as %i*panak-pars%i; with the usual for Scythian inversion in compound
                    words there is %ipars-panak%i in a Scythian proper name <mentioned
                        xml:lang="xsc"><lang/>
                        <w>Παρσπάνακος</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                                    type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>175,
                                235</biblScope></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                                    (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>175,
                                    235</biblScope></bibl>)</note></mentioned>. Beyond the bounds of
                    Scythian-Ossetic cf. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>pānak</w>
                        <gloss><q>thing that fences, protects</q></gloss></mentioned> (in compound
                    words), from which there is <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>p'anak'</w>
                        <gloss><q>cover</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>defence</q></gloss></mentioned> (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>šāb-panah</w>
                        <gloss><q>night shelter</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>shelter</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>pānah</w>
                        <gloss><q>wooden door bolt</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>wedge</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pāna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>guard</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>defence</q></gloss></mentioned> (in compound words), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pāna-</w></mentioned> id. Maybe, the word <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/>
                        <w>pon</w>
                        <gloss><q>roof</q></gloss></mentioned> is related to it as well. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>пано́к</w>
                        <gloss><q>board for cheap popular prints</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><w/><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">также</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">also</note>
                        <gloss><q>trough for meat mincing</q></gloss></mentioned> is probably a
                    Scythian heritage.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>175,
                            176, 199, 212, 236</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
